# CHANGELOG.md is fork-owned. protoTrader pulls *from* protoAgent (upstream), so
# the default `merge=union` is wrong here: it keeps BOTH sides of every conflict,
# which concatenates upstream's entire changelog into ours on every sync (the
# duplicate [0.14.0]/[0.15.x] sections we kept having to dedupe by hand).
# `merge=ours` keeps the fork's curated changelog and ignores upstream's churn;
# we summarize what a sync brings in one fork entry instead.
#
# NOTE: `merge=ours` needs the driver registered per-clone (it is NOT carried by
# .gitattributes alone). Run once after cloning (also belongs in CI / bootstrap):
#     git config merge.ours.driver true
CHANGELOG.md merge=ours
